-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"9668d23\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-af0ccb2 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"af0ccb2\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d096210 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"d096210\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Lidar_board_setup-1024x683.png\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-image-1795\" alt=\"lidar board setup\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Lidar_board_setup-1024x683.png 1024w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Lidar_board_setup-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Lidar_board_setup-768x512.png 768w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Lidar_board_setup.png 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"  title=\"LiDAR and Raspberry Pi Mounting Interface\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-897f16e e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"897f16e\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-65e4f32 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"65e4f32\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>As part of a university robotics project, I designed a custom mounting interface to integrate a LiDAR sensor and a Raspberry Pi onto a mobile robot. The objective was to provide a secure and compact mounting solution while simplifying the assembly of the robot.<\/p><p>The design included dedicated mounting holes for both the LiDAR sensor and Raspberry Pi, along with an integrated cable routing opening to allow neat cable management and reduce interference with the surrounding components. The mounting plate was designed to align the sensor correctly on the robot while remaining easy to manufacture using FDM 3D printing.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f135378 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"f135378\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b799dfa elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"b799dfa\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Project Information<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e9e2df1 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"e9e2df1\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cf01258 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"cf01258\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Software<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p>Fusion 360<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p><strong>Manufacturing<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p